The Premier Soccer League (PSL) has taken swift action and charged Kaizer Chiefs for bringing the League into disrepute and misconduct following the violent scenes at Moses Mabhida stadium on Saturday night. Angry fans went on the rampage and invaded the pitchâ€š assaulted some supporters and security officials and damaged property at the 2010 World Cup venue after Chiefs' 2-0 Nedbank Cup semifinal defeat to Free State Stars. Chiefs will appear before the PSL Disciplinary Committee on May 3 at 6pm.